Write a python script, which takes in a list of reddit thread links and spits out screenshots (in mobile view) of the main post and the top N (number should be changeable easily) comments.

Acceptance Criteria
Should accept a CSV of thread links
Should maintain proper folders for output images, which should be named as main.jpeg, comment1.jpeg, comment2.jpeg and so on.
Should also output out a JSON which contains the following (named metadata.json):

{
    "thread_heading": "heading text",
    "thread_body": "body text",
    "comments": [
        {
            "id": "comment_1", // should be the same as the file name in output
            "text": "comment text"
        }
    ]
}
